modules.description: Provides functions to create DNS queries, retrieve the underlying Unix domain socket for event monitoring, and fetch responses or cancel ongoing queries. Operates with query objects and Unix file descriptors to manage asynchronous DNS communication. Used to implement non-blocking DNS resolution with custom event loops.

Provides functions to perform DNS queries such as resolving service records, browsing for services, and querying host information using the macOS resolver. Works with data types including service names, domains, and host addresses. Used to integrate system-level DNS resolution into applications for consistent results with other macOS software.

manages asynchronous DNS communication through query objects and Unix sockets, enabling non-blocking resolution and event-driven monitoring. It supports creating queries, accessing underlying file descriptors for event loops, and handling responses or cancellations. Key data types include query objects and Unix file descriptors, with operations for query management and socket interaction. Examples include implementing custom DNS resolvers and integrating DNS lookups into event-driven applications.
